I"–<p>#OFFGRID
A simple offgrid solar system can be created using a Raspberry Pi (or equivalent), a standard 12v solar panel with MPTT and a battery. This system</p>

<p>##Raspberry Pi
Raspberry Pi provides a Linux environment which is equivalent to a traditional VPS. A regular server stack can be built using Apache or Nginx, with PHP, Python, MariaDB, MongoDB or any other services needed.</p>
<ol>
  <li>Raspberry Pi 4 with up to 8gb:</li>
  <li>Raspberry Pi A+:</li>
  <li>Raspberry Pi Zero 2 W.</li>
</ol>

<p>##Solar system and battery
A regular solar system includes a solar panel, a MPPT regulator, a battery, and some cables to connect all together.</p>

